---
description: Skeleton loading states must match the real component dimensions and live in their own files
globs: "**/loading.tsx,**/*Skeleton*,**/*skeleton*"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Skeleton Loading

A skeleton that doesn't match the real component causes layout shift — the page "jumps" when the skeleton is replaced. This is jarring, hurts CLS score, and looks unprofessional.

### Skeletons must mirror real component dimensions

When writing or updating a skeleton, open the real component side-by-side and match:

- **Outer layout**: same flex/grid direction, same `gap-*`, same `p-*` and `m-*`
- **Image/avatar areas**: same `w-*`, `h-*`, `aspect-*`, `rounded-*`
- **Text line heights**: `h-4` for body, `h-5` for headings — match what the real text renders as
- **Spacing between regions**: `mb-*` and `mt-*` must match between skeleton and real card

```tsx
// wrong - skeleton uses mb-3, real card uses mb-2
<div className="mb-3">
  <Skeleton className="h-32 w-full" />
</div>

// correct - aligned with the real card
<div className="mb-2">
  <Skeleton className="h-32 w-full" />
</div>
```

### Always update the skeleton when you update the layout

If you change spacing, padding, or section order in a component, update its corresponding skeleton in the same PR/change. They are a pair.

### Use only standard Tailwind widths

Non-standard Tailwind widths (e.g. `w-18`, `w-22`) are not part of the default scale and silently compute to `0` or the wrong value depending on Tailwind version.

```tsx
// wrong - w-18 is not a default Tailwind class
<Skeleton className="w-18 h-6" />

// correct - use a standard width or arbitrary value
<Skeleton className="w-20 h-6" />
<Skeleton className="w-[72px] h-6" />
```

Always verify a Tailwind class exists in the default v4 scale before using it.

### Skeletons must live in their own files

Never export a skeleton component from a `"use client"` file that also contains the real component. This forces the browser to download the full component implementation just to show the skeleton.

```
// wrong structure
src/components/home/PersonalizedDashboard.tsx  ← "use client", exports both real + skeleton

// correct structure
src/components/home/PersonalizedDashboard.tsx       ← "use client", real component only
src/components/home/PersonalizedDashboardSkeleton.tsx ← no "use client", skeleton only
```

The skeleton file should have **no** `"use client"` directive unless the skeleton itself requires client interactivity (it almost never does).

### Loading fallbacks in Suspense

When using React `<Suspense>` with a skeleton fallback, the fallback component must be importable without pulling in any client-side dependencies:

```tsx
// correct - skeleton is a pure RSC, no client bundle cost
import { ProductCardSkeleton } from "@/components/products/skeletons/ProductCardSkeleton"

<Suspense fallback={<ProductCardSkeleton />}>
  <ProductCard id={id} />
</Suspense>
```
